com.camerontec.catalys.core.session

Interface IConnectionPoint

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IConfigurable, IRegisterable, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConnectionPoint

    public interface IConnectionPoint
extends Serializable, IConfigurable
    This uniquely defines a point of communication with an external counter party.

    A Session will take place at this connection point.

    The connection point is defined by the IParty with whom we are communicating, the IParty by which we are known to them and our unique identifier of the application which is managing the connection.

    Note that this allows us to have multiple connection points with the same external party, distinguished by how we are known to that party or by which of our applications is managing the connection.

      • toFileString

        String toFileString()
        Returns a unique String for this object in a format suitable for use as a file name.

        This is useful if you are storing related information in files.

        In particular the returned String should not contain any of the following characters... :,=*?/\'"

        If you avoid the above characters, the String should also work as a valid JMX name.

        Returns:
        a unique String for this object in a format suitable for use as a file name.
